To solve this, we first distribute the $2$ into the second complex number.
\begin{align*} (5-4i)-2(3+6i) &= 5-4i-6-12i \end{align*}

Now,
\begin{align*} 5-4i-6-12i &= 5-6 -4i-12i\\&=-1-16i\end{align*}

So
<a>answer</a> <b>-1-16i</b>.

